generate_verti...dge_constraint(25.10)  generate_verti...dge_constraint(25.10)

Name
       generate_vertical_cell_edge_constraint  -  Generates the bottom and top
       cell edge constraints for 10nm libraries to avoid vertical  cell  abut-
       ment that may cause pin access issue on M1 and M2

Syntax
       generate_vertical_cell_edge_constraint

       [-help]

       {-file <tclFile> | -updateDB }

       [[-check_m2_only ] | [-check_m2_to_m1_only ]]

       Generates  the  bottom and top cell edge constraints for 10nm libraries
       to avoid vertical cell abutment that may cause pin access issue  on  M1
       and  M2.  The vertical M2 fat PIN or OBS has impact on the abutted cell
       when it is near to the top and bottom boundaries. It can cause DRC vio-
       lations between M2 PIN/OBS, block some of the M1 pin access  points  in
       the abutted cell, and make router hard to access those M1 PINs.

       The following graphic show an example of how fat M2 Pin/OBS may block 3
       or 6 access points.

       The  generate_vertical_cell_edge_constraint  command generates vertical
       cell edge constraints based on the cell libraries and LEF rules. Placer
       is aware of these constraints and avoids the bad placement patterns.

Parameters
       -check_m2_only
              Checks M2 to M2 pins only in abutted  2  cells  when  generating
              cell edge constraints.

       -check_m2_to_m1_only
              Checks  M2  to  M1  pins only in abutted 2 cells when generating
              cell edge constraints.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for each generate_vertical_cell_edge_constraint para-
              meter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man  generate_vertical_cell_edge_con-
              straint.

       -file <tclFile>
              Specifies file name to output vertical tcl constraint.

       -updateDB
              Updates the constraints to DB.

       Note:

              * You must specify -file or -updateDB.

              * The -file option is for the debug mode, and you need to source
                the tcl file to let placer know about the constraints.

              * The  -updated  option is for the standard flow usage. It reads
                the constraints automatically.

